For a point mass&nbsp;\(M\), the magnitude of the <b>force of attraction</b>&nbsp;on a test mass&nbsp;\(m\)&nbsp;at distance&nbsp;\(r\)&nbsp;from&nbsp;\(M\)&nbsp;is given by&nbsp;<b>Newton's law of gravitation</b>.\[F=\frac{GMm}{r^2}\]Therefore the magnitude of the gravitational field strength at distance&nbsp;\(r\)&nbsp;is\[g=\frac{F}{m}=\frac{GM}{r^2}\]<br>